modules.description: This module handles OCaml AST transformations for generating JavaScript interop code. It provides rewriters for module expressions, type declarations, and conversion functions between OCaml and JavaScript representations, operating directly on Parsetree elements like core_type, expression, and signature. It is used to implement JS-of-OCaml bindings, enabling precise control over type and module transformations during compilation.

This module defines configuration flags for attribute and location checking during JavaScript API generation. It works with boolean values to control validation behavior in the PPX processing pipeline. Concrete use cases include enabling stricter attribute validation or location tracking when generating OCaml bindings for JavaScript code.
